dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-authe.name: authenticatorData
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-authe.summary: The authenticatorData property of the AuthenticatorAssertionResponse interface returns an ArrayBuffer containing information from the authenticator such as the Relying Party ID Hash (rpIdHash), a signature counter, test of user presence, user verification flags, and any extensions processed by the authenticator.
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-authe.title: AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.authenticatorData

dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-signa.name: signature
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-signa.summary: The signature read-only property of the AuthenticatorAssertionResponse interface is an ArrayBuffer object which is the signature of the authenticator for both AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.authenticatorData and a SHA-256 hash of the client data (AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.clientDataJSON).
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-signa.title: AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.signature

dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-userh.name: userHandle
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-userh.summary: The userHandle read-only property of the AuthenticatorAssertionResponse interface is an ArrayBuffer object which is an opaque identifier for the given user. Such an identifier can be used by the relying party's server to link the user account with its corresponding credentials and other data.
dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-userh.title: AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.userHandle

iface-authenticatorassertionresponse.name: AuthenticatorAssertionResponse
iface-authenticatorassertionresponse.summary: The AuthenticatorAssertionResponse interface of the Web Authentication API is returned by CredentialsContainer.get() when a PublicKeyCredential is passed, and provides proof to a service that it has a key pair and that the authentication request is valid and approved.
iface-authenticatorassertionresponse.title: AuthenticatorAssertionResponse

dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-att.name: attestationObject
dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-att.summary: The attestationObject property of the AuthenticatorAttestationResponse interface returns an ArrayBuffer containing the new public key, as well as signature over the entire attestationObject with a private key that is stored in the authenticator when it is manufactured.
dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-att.title: AuthenticatorAttestationResponse.attestationObject

dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-get.name: getTransports
dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-get.summary: getTransports() is a method of the AuthenticatorAttestationResponse interface that returns an Array containing strings describing the different transports which may be used by the authenticator.
dom-authenticatorattestationresponse-get.title: AuthenticatorAttestationResponse.getTransports()

authenticatorattestationresponse.name: AuthenticatorAttestationResponse
authenticatorattestationresponse.summary: The AuthenticatorAttestationResponse interface of the Web Authentication API is returned by CredentialsContainer.create() when a PublicKeyCredential is passed, and provides a cryptographic root of trust for the new key pair that has been generated. This response should be sent to the relying party's server to complete the creation of the credential.
authenticatorattestationresponse.title: AuthenticatorAttestationResponse

dom-authenticatorresponse-clientdatajson.name: clientDataJSON
dom-authenticatorresponse-clientdatajson.summary: The clientDataJSON property of the AuthenticatorResponse interface stores a JSON string in an ArrayBuffer, representing the client data that was passed to CredentialsContainer.create() or CredentialsContainer.get(). This property is only accessed on one of the child objects of AuthenticatorResponse, specifically AuthenticatorAttestationResponse or AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.
dom-authenticatorresponse-clientdatajson.title: AuthenticatorResponse.clientDataJSON

authenticatorresponse.name: AuthenticatorResponse
authenticatorresponse.summary: The AuthenticatorResponse interface of the Web Authentication API is the base interface for interfaces that provide a cryptographic root of trust for a key pair. The child interfaces include information from the browser such as the challenge origin and either may be returned from PublicKeyCredential.response.
authenticatorresponse.title: AuthenticatorResponse

dom-publickeycredential-getclientextensi.name: getClientExtensionResults
dom-publickeycredential-getclientextensi.summary: getClientExtensionResults() is a method of the PublicKeyCredential interface that returns an ArrayBuffer which contains a map between the extensions identifiers and their results after having being processed by the client.
dom-publickeycredential-getclientextensi.title: PublicKeyCredential.getClientExtensionResults()

dom-publickeycredential-isuserverifyingp.name: isUserVerifyingPlatformAuthenticatorAvailable
dom-publickeycredential-isuserverifyingp.summary: isUserVerifyingPlatformAuthenticatorAvailable() is a static method of the PublicKeyCredential interface that returns a Promise which resolves to true if a user-verifying platform authenticator is available.
dom-publickeycredential-isuserverifyingp.title: PublicKeyCredential.isUserVerifyingPlatformAuthenticatorAvailable()

dom-publickeycredential-rawid.name: rawId
dom-publickeycredential-rawid.summary: The rawId read-only property of the PublicKeyCredential interface is an ArrayBuffer object containing the identifier of the credentials.
dom-publickeycredential-rawid.title: PublicKeyCredential.rawId

dom-publickeycredential-response.name: response
dom-publickeycredential-response.summary: The response read-only property of the PublicKeyCredential interface is an AuthenticatorResponse object which is sent from the authenticator to the user agent for the creation/fetching of credentials. The information contained in this response will be used by the relying party's server to verify the demand is legitimate.
dom-publickeycredential-response.title: PublicKeyCredential.response

iface-pkcredential.name: PublicKeyCredential
iface-pkcredential.summary: The PublicKeyCredential interface provides information about a public key / private key pair, which is a credential for logging in to a service using an un-phishable and data-breach resistant asymmetric key pair instead of a password. It inherits from Credential, and was created by the Web Authentication API extension to the Credential Management API. Other interfaces that inherit from Credential are PasswordCredential and FederatedCredential.
iface-pkcredential.title: PublicKeyCredential

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.name: attestation
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.summary: attestation is an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary. This is a string whose value indicates the preference regarding the attestation transport, between the authenticator, the client and the relying party.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.attestation

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.name: authenticatorSelection
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.summary: authenticatorSelection, an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary, is an object giving criteria to filter out the authenticators to be used for the creation operation.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-a.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.authenticatorSelection

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-c.name: challenge
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-c.summary: The challenge property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary is a BufferSource used as a cryptographic challenge. This is randomly generated then sent from the relying party's server. This value (among other client data) will be signed by the authenticator, using its private key, and must be sent back for verification to the server as part of AuthenticatorAttestationResponse.attestationObject.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-c.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.challenge

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-e.name: excludeCredentials
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-e.summary: excludeCredentials, an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary, is an Array whose elements are descriptors for the public keys already existing for a given user. This is provided by the relying party's server if it wants to prevent creation of new credentials for an existing user.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-e.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.excludeCredentials

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.name: extensions
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.summary: extensions, an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary, is an object providing the client extensions and their input values.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.extensions

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.name: extensions
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.summary: extensions, an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary, is an object providing the client extensions and their input values.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ex.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.extensions

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-p.name: pubKeyCredParams
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-p.summary: The pubKeyCredParams property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary is an Array whose elements are objects describing the desired features of the credential to be created. These objects define the type of public-key and the algorithm used for cryptographic signature operations.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-p.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.pubKeyCredParams

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-r.name: rp
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-r.summary: The rp property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary is an object describing the relying party which requested the credential creation (via navigator.credentials.create()).
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-r.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.rp

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-t.name: timeout
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-t.summary: The timeout property, of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary, represents an hint, given in milliseconds, for the time the script is willing to wait for the completion of the creation operation.
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-t.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.timeout

dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-u.name: user
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-u.summary: The user property of the PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary is an object describing the user account for which the credentials are generated (via navigator.credentials.create()).
dom-publickeycredentialcreationoptions-u.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions.user

dictdef-publickeycredentialcreationoptio.name: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions
dictdef-publickeycredentialcreationoptio.summary: The PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary of the Web Authentication API holds options passed to navigators.credentials.create() in order to create a PublicKeyCredential.
dictdef-publickeycredentialcreationoptio.title: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-al.name: allowCredentials
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-al.summary: allowCredentials is an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary which indicates the existing credentials acceptable for retrieval. This is an Array of credential descriptors.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-al.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.allowCredentials

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ch.name: challenge
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ch.summary: The challenge property of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary is a BufferSource used as a cryptographic challenge. This is randomly generated then sent from the relying party's server. This value (among other client data) will be signed by the authenticator's private key and produce AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.signature which should be sent back to the server as part of the response.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ch.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.challenge

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-rp.name: rpId
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-rp.summary: The rpId property, of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary, is an optional property which indicates the relying party's identifier as a USVString. Its value can only be a suffix of the current origin's domain. For example, if you are browsing on foo.example.com, the rpId value may be "example.com" but not "bar.org" or "baz.example.com".
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-rp.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.rpId

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ti.name: timeout
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ti.summary: The timeout property, of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary, represents an hint, given in milliseconds, for the time the script is willing to wait for the completion of the retrieval operation.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-ti.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.timeout

dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-us.name: userVerification
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-us.summary: userVerification is an optional property of the PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions. This is a string which indicates how the user verification should be part of the authentication process.
dom-publickeycredentialrequestoptions-us.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions.userVerification

dictdef-publickeycredentialrequestoption.name: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions
dictdef-publickeycredentialrequestoption.summary: The PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary of the Web Authentication API holds the options passed to navigator.credentials.get() in order to fetch a given PublicKeyCredential.
dictdef-publickeycredentialrequestoption.title: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions

sctn-feature-policy.name: publickey-credentials-get
sctn-feature-policy.summary: The HTTP Feature-Policy header publickey-credentials-get directive controls whether the current document is allowed to access Web Authentcation API to create new public-key credentials, i.e, via navigator.credentials.get({publicKey: ..., ...}).
sctn-feature-policy.title: Feature-Policy: publickey-credentials-get
